# State Management

Use this rule with `.ai/lifecycle/think.md`, `.ai/lifecycle/plan.md`, `.ai/lifecycle/build.md`, and `.ai/lifecycle/review.md`.

Before adding state, decide whether it is local UI state, shared client state, server state, URL state, or persisted state.

{{#if (eq stateManagement "none")}}
- Prefer **local component state** and framework primitives (Context sparingly).
- Avoid prop drilling more than 2–3 levels — lift state or use composition.
{{/if}}

{{#if hasRedux}}
- Use **Redux Toolkit** slices; colocate slice + selectors; avoid large monolithic stores.
- Prefer RTK Query only if selected as data layer; otherwise keep queries separate.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasZustand}}
- One store per domain; export selectors; avoid storing non-serializable objects unless intentional.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasJotai}}
- Prefer atoms per concern; derive with `atom` + read-only dependencies.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasRecoil}}
- Avoid cross-atom cycles; document atom families for lists.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasPinia}}
- Setup stores with `defineStore`; prefer composition-style stores for complex domains.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasNgRx}}
- Actions/reducers/effects separated; selectors for derived data; keep facades thin.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasSvelteStores}}
- Use `writable` + `derived`; unsubscribe in `onDestroy` when subscribing manually.
{{/if}}
{{#if hasMobX}}
- Prefer `observer` boundaries; keep actions explicit; avoid mutating observables outside actions.
{{/if}}

## SSR / hydration

{{#if hasMetaFramework}}
- Ensure server and client render **consistent initial state**; avoid reading `window` during first paint on server bundles.
{{/if}}

## Ownership Rules

- Keep state local when only one component subtree needs it.
- Lift state only to the nearest common owner.
- Use URL/search params for shareable navigation or filter state.
- Use server-state tooling for cache, invalidation, and async data; do not duplicate it in client stores.
- Persist state only when the product behavior requires it.

## Must Avoid

- Global stores for one-off form or modal state.
- Derived state that can be computed from props, URL, or server data.
- Silent persistence of sensitive values.
- Hydration-sensitive state reads during server render.

## Acceptance Criteria

- State owner and lifecycle are named.
- Reset, loading, error, and stale states are handled.
- Tests or manual checks cover state transitions that affect the user flow.
